<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Serving-man" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Serving-man,</orth> a servant: <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.81" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 2, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.1.76" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 1, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.3.12" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 12</bibl>. Term of gallantry (cf. <emph>Servant</emph>): <cit><quote>a s. proud in heart and mind, that curled my hair,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.87" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 87</bibl></cit> <emph>(cavaliere servente?).</emph>
